                           <desc>Words from the text on the same folio copied in a crude hand</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <locus target="#170r #170v" facs="173 174">Fols. 170r, 170v</locus>
                           <desc>Unintelligible note</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                          <locus target="#7r #26r" facs="010 029">Fols. 7r, 26r</locus>
                          <desc>The scribe rarely has to complete a line of text on another line.
                            The challenge is addressed mainly through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size.
                            Where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., ff. 7r, 26r, etc.)</desc>
                          </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                          <locus target="#10r #76v #85r #90r #91r #95v #115v #116v #118r" facs="013 080 088 093 094 099 119 120 121">Fols. 10r, 76v, 85r, 90r, 91r, 95v, 115v, 116v, 118r</locus>
                          <desc>etc., overlooked words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                          </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                          <locus target="#99v #142r" facs="103 145">Fols. 99v, 142r</locus>
                          <desc>Overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                          </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                          <locus target="#136v" facs="140"> f. 136v, line 6</locus>
                          <desc>Overlooked lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="e9">
                          <locus target="#49r" facs="052">Fol. 49r</locus>
                          <desc>The reinforcement strip sewn around quire seven is from a rejected leaf of another book and has text on it</desc>
                      </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                          <locus target="#iiiv(erso) #136v" facs="004 140">Fols. iiiv(erso), 136v</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang="gez">አባ፡ እማም፡</foreign>, and <foreign xml:lang="gez">አባ፡ አለማየሁ፡</foreign> of Morät</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e10">
                           <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                           <desc>blank</desc>
                      </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to the wooden boards, rough-hewn boards covered with leather, a sheet of parchment is wrapped around all the quires to cover the spine.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
